==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Duration
<hw>Du*ra"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OF.
<ets>duration</ets>. See <er>Dure</er>.]</ety> <def>The state or quality
of lasting; continuance in time; the portion of time during which
anything exists.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>It was proposed that the <qex>duration</qex> of Parliament should
be limited.</q> <rj><qau>Macaulay.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Soon shall have passed our own human <qex>duration</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>D. Webster.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Durative</ent>⟦br⟧
